  "content": {
    "problemStatement": "Sereja has an array **A** consisting of **N** integers. Sereja has **M** queries **(Li, Ri)**, and for each query Sereja wants to find the length of the longest increasing subsequence in the array **A[Li], A[Li + 1], ..., A[Ri]**. \n\n\n\nHelp Sereja find the answer for each query.",
    "constraints": [
      "**1** ≤ **T** ≤ **10**",
      "**1** ≤ **A[i]**, **M**, **N**",
      "Let **S** be sum of all **A[i]** in whole file.",
      "**1** ≤ **S** ≤ ** 1000000 **",
      "**1** ≤ **Li** ≤ **Ri** ≤ ** N **",
      "**1** ≤ sum of all **M** per file  ≤ ** 1000000 **",
      "Subtasks",
      "**Subtask #1:**  **1** ≤ **N**, **M** ≤ ** 100 ** (15 points)",
      "**Subtask #2:**  **1** ≤ **N**, **M** ≤ ** 1000 ** (15 points)",
      "**Subtask #3:**   ** original constraints ** (70 points)",
      "Example**Input:**",
      "1",
      "5 3",
      "2 5 1 2 3",
      "1 5",
      "1 3",
      "2 4",
      "**Output:**",
      "3",
      "2",
      "2"
    ],
    "inputFormat": "The first line of the input contains an integer **T** denoting the number of test cases.\n\nThe description of **T** test cases follows. \n\nEach test case starts with two integers **N**, **M**. \n\nThe next line contains the numbers **A[1], A[2], ..., A[N]**. The next **M** lines contains the pairs **Li, Ri**, which are the queries.",
    "outputFormat": "For each test case, output **M** lines - the answer for each query.",
